Reasoning: The paper deals with network coding and network alignment in wireline networks with delays, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of local encoding kernels (LEKs) and block time varying LEKs, which are relevant to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of transform approach, which is related to signal processing (cs.SP) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the feasibility of network alignment, which is relevant to computer communication (cs.CC).
